http://purl.org/dc/terms/Agent.label: Agent
http://purl.org/dc/terms/Agent.definition: A resource that acts or has the power to act.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/BibliographicRe.label: Bibliographic Resource
http://purl.org/dc/terms/BibliographicRe.definition: A book, article, or other documentary resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/MediaType.label: Media Type
http://purl.org/dc/terms/MediaType.definition: A file format or physical medium.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/Frequency.label: Frequency
http://purl.org/dc/terms/Frequency.definition: A rate at which something recurs.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/Jurisdiction.label: Jurisdiction
http://purl.org/dc/terms/Jurisdiction.definition: The extent or range of judicial, law enforcement, or other authority.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/LocationPeriodO.label: Location, Period, or Jurisdiction
http://purl.org/dc/terms/LocationPeriodO.definition: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/LicenseDocument.label: License Document
http://purl.org/dc/terms/LicenseDocument.definition: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/RightsStatement.label: Rights Statement
http://purl.org/dc/terms/RightsStatement.definition: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/LinguisticSyste.label: Linguistic System
http://purl.org/dc/terms/LinguisticSyste.definition: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/Location.label: Location
http://purl.org/dc/terms/Location.definition: A spatial region or named place.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/MethodOfAccrual.label: Method of Accrual
http://purl.org/dc/terms/MethodOfAccrual.definition: A method by which resources are added to a collection.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/MethodOfInstruc.label: Method of Instruction
http://purl.org/dc/terms/MethodOfInstruc.definition: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime.label: Period of Time
http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime.definition: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/Policy.label: Policy
http://purl.org/dc/terms/Policy.definition: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/ProvenanceState.label: Provenance Statement
http://purl.org/dc/terms/ProvenanceState.definition: Any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/SizeOrDuration.label: Size or Duration
http://purl.org/dc/terms/SizeOrDuration.definition: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/Standard.label: Standard
http://purl.org/dc/terms/Standard.definition: A reference point against which other things can be evaluated or compared.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified.label: Date Modified
http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified.definition: Date on which the resource was changed.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher.label: Publisher
http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher.definition: An entity responsible for making the resource available.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/title.label: Title
http://purl.org/dc/terms/title.definition: A name given to the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued.label: Date Issued
http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued.definition: Date of formal issuance of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights.label: Access Rights
http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights.definition: Information about who access the resource or an indication of its security status.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/rights.label: Rights
http://purl.org/dc/terms/rights.definition: Information about rights held in and over the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualMethod.label: Accrual Method
http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualMethod.definition: The method by which items are added to a collection.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualPeriodic.label: Accrual Periodicity
http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualPeriodic.definition: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualPolicy.label: Accrual Policy
http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualPolicy.definition: The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/alternative.label: Alternative Title
http://purl.org/dc/terms/alternative.definition: An alternative name for the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/audience.label: Audience
http://purl.org/dc/terms/audience.definition: A class of agents for whom the resource is intended or useful.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/available.label: Date Available
http://purl.org/dc/terms/available.definition: Date that the resource became or will become available.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/date.label: Date
http://purl.org/dc/terms/date.definition: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/bibliographicCi.label: Bibliographic Citation
http://purl.org/dc/terms/bibliographicCi.definition: A bibliographic reference for the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier.label: Identifier
http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier.definition: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo.label: Conforms To
http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo.definition: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor.label: Contributor
http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor.definition: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/coverage.label: Coverage
http://purl.org/dc/terms/coverage.definition: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, spatial applicability of the resource, or jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/created.label: Date Created
http://purl.org/dc/terms/created.definition: Date of creation of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator.label: Creator
http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator.definition: An entity responsible for making the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/dateAccepted.label: Date Accepted
http://purl.org/dc/terms/dateAccepted.definition: Date of acceptance of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/dateCopyrighted.label: Date Copyrighted
http://purl.org/dc/terms/dateCopyrighted.definition: Date of copyright of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/dateSubmitted.label: Date Submitted
http://purl.org/dc/terms/dateSubmitted.definition: Date of submission of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/educationLevel.label: Audience Education Level
http://purl.org/dc/terms/educationLevel.definition: A class of agents, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/extent.label: Extent
http://purl.org/dc/terms/extent.definition: The size or duration of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/format.label: Format
http://purl.org/dc/terms/format.definition: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasFormat.label: Has Format
http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasFormat.definition: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasPart.label: Has Part
http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasPart.definition: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasVersion.label: Has Version
http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasVersion.definition: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/instructionalMe.label: Instructional Method
http://purl.org/dc/terms/instructionalMe.definition: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/isFormatOf.label: Is Format Of
http://purl.org/dc/terms/isFormatOf.definition: A pre-existing related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf.label: Is Part Of
http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf.definition: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/isReferencedBy.label: Is Referenced By
http://purl.org/dc/terms/isReferencedBy.definition: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/isReplacedBy.label: Is Replaced By
http://purl.org/dc/terms/isReplacedBy.definition: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/isRequiredBy.label: Is Required By
http://purl.org/dc/terms/isRequiredBy.definition: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/isVersionOf.label: Is Version Of
http://purl.org/dc/terms/isVersionOf.definition: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/license.label: License
http://purl.org/dc/terms/license.definition: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/mediator.label: Mediator
http://purl.org/dc/terms/mediator.definition: An entity that mediates access to the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/medium.label: Medium
http://purl.org/dc/terms/medium.definition: The material or physical carrier of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/provenance.label: Provenance
http://purl.org/dc/terms/provenance.definition: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/references.label: References
http://purl.org/dc/terms/references.definition: A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/replaces.label: Replaces
http://purl.org/dc/terms/replaces.definition: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/requires.label: Requires
http://purl.org/dc/terms/requires.definition: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/rightsHolder.label: Rights Holder
http://purl.org/dc/terms/rightsHolder.definition: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.label: Source
http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.definition: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/tableOfContents.label: Table Of Contents
http://purl.org/dc/terms/tableOfContents.definition: A list of subunits of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/type.label: Type
http://purl.org/dc/terms/type.definition: The nature or genre of the resource.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/valid.label: Date Valid
http://purl.org/dc/terms/valid.definition: Date (often a range) of validity of a resource.
